    "extras": [
      "Indian passport holders can currently visit Malaysia visa-free for short leisure trips; still complete the latest digital arrival form before departure.",
      "Grab is the single most useful Malaysia app for airport rides, city hops, and even food delivery across Kuala Lumpur, Penang, Langkawi, and Kota Kinabalu.",
      "Kuala Lumpur and Penang are especially easy for vegetarian Indian travelers thanks to Brickfields and Little India restaurant clusters.",
      "Jonker Walk is best on Friday to Sunday evenings in Malacca, while many nearby shops feel quieter on Tuesdays.",
      "Langkawi is duty-free, so chocolates, perfumes, and alcohol are often cheapest there rather than in Kuala Lumpur or Penang.",
      "This route stays easiest on Malaysia’s west coast; northeast monsoon affects the east coast more, while September–October can still feel hazy in cities."
    ],
